text:
We had some skewers and the sauerkraut fish. Skewers are competitively priced and nothing to really wow about similar to most shops. The pig intestines on skewer was not good as it was not well cleaned.

The fish was a very decent serving of the price, nice and neat place and service was decent. Has a large selection of alcoholic beverages.

The minimum spending is S$200 for the private room. The food was delicious. The ambience is cosy. Fast and polite service. Other than the food, I had a great time singing KTV in the private room. Good sound system.

My second visiting. First time was in the evening, didnâ€™t mange to get the promo price but still find the price is reasonable. This time round came for lunch. Got the grilled fish at $14.40 and chilli chicken for $1.99. Really value for money. Food portion is reasonable and taste is good. Will come again.
Nice cozy place with friends or family members. They still have promotions for dinning in their restaurant for meat sticks at $1. I love most is their white pearl rice it's so nice and firm.
The food is great. One of the better food I have tried. Watch out for their fish 50% promotion as well! Great place to dine.
